workflow.name: Automate job applications with Gemini AI, Notion tracking & multi-platform search
workflow.description:
## üéØ Smart Job Hunter Pro - AI-Powered Multi-Platform Job Automation

Transform your job search with this comprehensive n8n workflow that automatically searches, analyzes, and applies to relevant positions across multiple job platforms. Perfect for **developers**, **engineers**, and **tech professionals** looking to streamline their job hunting process.

## ‚ú® Key Features

- **üîÑ Multi-Platform Job Search**: Simultaneously searches Jooble, JobStreet, Indeed, and WhatJobs APIs
- **ü§ñ AI-Powered Job Analysis**: Uses Google Gemini AI to analyze job compatibility and generate tailored cover letters
- **üìä Smart Scoring System**: Automatically scores job matches based on your skills and requirements
- **üìù Auto-Apply Threshold**: Only applies to jobs above your specified compatibility score
- **üìã Notion Integration**: Automatically tracks applications in organized Notion database
- **üí¨ Telegram Notifications**: Real-time alerts for high-match job opportunities
- **‚òÅÔ∏è Google Drive Storage**: Saves personalized cover letters for each application
- **‚ö†Ô∏è Error Handling**: Comprehensive error tracking with Telegram notifications
- **‚è∞ Automated Scheduling**: Runs every 8 hours to find fresh opportunities

## üõ† What This Workflow Does

1. **Scheduled Search**: Automatically searches multiple job platforms every 8 hours
2. **Data Normalization**: Standardizes job data from different API sources
3. **AI Analysis**: Gemini AI evaluates each job posting against your skills profile
4. **Smart Filtering**: Only processes jobs above your compatibility threshold (default: 75%)
5. **Application Tracking**: Creates detailed records in Notion with match scores and status
6. **Instant Alerts**: Sends Telegram notifications for promising opportunities
7. **Cover Letter Generation**: AI creates personalized cover letters for each position
8. **Document Management**: Automatically saves all cover letters to Google Drive

## üîß Required Integrations

- **Job APIs**: Jooble API, WhatJobs API (JobStreet & Indeed use web scraping)
- **AI Service**: Google Gemini API for job analysis
- **Productivity**: Notion database for application tracking
- **Communication**: Telegram bot for notifications
- **Storage**: Google Drive for cover letter management

## üí° Perfect For

- **Software Developers** seeking JavaScript, React, Node.js positions
- **Full-Stack Engineers** wanting automated job discovery
- **Tech Professionals** needing organized application tracking
- **Remote Workers** searching across multiple platforms
- **Career Changers** looking for systematic job hunting

## üéõ Customizable Variables

- **Job Keywords**: Define your target roles and skills
- **Location & Radius**: Set geographic search parameters
- **Auto-Apply Threshold**: Control compatibility score requirements
- **Results Limit**: Adjust number of jobs per platform
- **Schedule Frequency**: Modify search intervals

## üìà Benefits

- **Save 10+ hours weekly** on manual job searching
- **Never miss opportunities** with automated monitoring
- **Professional application tracking** with detailed analytics
- **Personalized cover letters** for every application
- **Instant notifications** for high-match positions
- **Complete audit trail** of all job search activities

## üöÄ Getting Started

1. Import the workflow to your n8n instance
2. Configure API credentials for all job platforms
3. Set up Notion database with provided template structure
4. Create Telegram bot and Google Drive folder
5. Customize job search parameters for your profile
6. Activate workflow and start receiving opportunities!

## üìù Additional Notes

- Uses placeholder credentials for security (`{{PLACEHOLDER_API_KEY}}`)
- Comprehensive error handling prevents workflow failures  
- Includes detailed setup instructions via sticky notes
- Optimized for Indonesian job market (JobStreet.co.id)
- Easily adaptable for other regions and job types

Perfect for **developers**, **engineers**, and **automation enthusiasts** who want to leverage AI and n8n's power to dominate their job search process! üöÄ

parameters.content:
## üìã Complete Installation & Usage

### **Pre-Requirements**
Before importing this workflow, ensure you have:
- n8n instance (self-hosted or cloud)
- Admin access to configure credentials
- Valid API keys for job portals
- Integration accounts (Google, Notion, Telegram)

### **Step 1: Import Workflow**
1. **Download the Automated-Job-Finder.json file** to your local computer
2. **Open your n8n instance** (https://your-n8n-domain.com)
3. **Navigate to Workflows** ‚Üí Click **"Import from file"**
4. **Select the JSON file** and click **"Import"**
5. **Rename the workflow** to your preferred name (e.g., "Smart-Job-Hunter-Pro")

### **Step 2: Configure Required API Credentials**

#### **Jooble API Setup:**
- Visit [Jooble Partner API](https://jooble.org/api/about)
- Register for free API access and get your API key
- Replace `{{PLACEHOLDER_JOOBLE_API_KEY}}` with your actual key

#### **WhatJobs API Setup:**
- Visit [WhatJobs API Documentation](https://developer.whatjobs.com)
- Create developer account and generate API token
- Replace `{{PLACEHOLDER_WHATJOBS_API_TOKEN}}` with your token

#### **Google Gemini AI Setup:**
- Go to [Google AI Studio](https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
- Create new API key for job analysis
- In n8n: Add "Google PaLM API" credential with your key

#### **Notion Database Setup:**
1. Create Notion database with properties:
   - **Title**: Text
   - **Company**: Text  
   - **Status**: Select (Applied, Interview, Rejected, Offer)
   - **Match Score**: Number
   - **Applied Date**: Date
   - **Job URL**: URL
   - **Location**: Text
   - **Source**: Select (Jooble, JobStreet, Indeed, WhatJobs)

2. Get database ID from URL and replace `{{PLACEHOLDER_NOTION_DATABASE_ID}}`
3. Create Notion integration and share database access

#### **Telegram Bot Setup:**
- Message @BotFather to create new bot
- Get bot token and chat ID
- Replace `{{PLACEHOLDER_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID}}` with your chat ID
- Configure Telegram credential in n8n

#### **Google Drive Setup:**
- Enable Google Drive API in Google Cloud Console
- Create "Job Applications" folder
- Get folder ID and replace `{{PLACEHOLDER_GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID}}`
- Setup OAuth2 credentials in n8n

### **Step 3: Customize Job Search Parameters**

Edit the "Set Job Variables" node with your preferences:

```javascript
{
  "job_keywords": "your target roles and skills",
  "auto_apply_threshold": 75,  // AI compatibility score threshold
  "location": "Your Country/City", 
  "radius": "50",  // Search radius in km
  "max_results_per_source": "10"  // Jobs per API source
}
```

### **Step 4: Test and Activate**

1. **Manual Test**: Click "Execute Workflow" to test all integrations
2. **Verify Results**: Check Notion database, Telegram notifications, and Google Drive
3. **Schedule Configuration**: Default runs every 8 hours (customizable)
4. **Activate Workflow**: Toggle to "Active" status for automated execution

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
